        <div class="faq-item">
          <div class="faq-q">How much protein does a man over 40 need per day?</div>
          <div class="faq-a">Most research supports 1.2–1.6 g of protein per kilogram of bodyweight per day for men over 40 — roughly double the standard RDA. For a 185-pound man, that's 100–130g daily. A practical working target is 1.4 g/kg, which lands most men in the right range without being difficult to hit.</div>
