          <div class="faq-q">Why do protein needs increase after 40?</div>
          <div class="faq-a">After 40, muscles become less efficient at using protein — a phenomenon called anabolic resistance. You need more protein input to get the same muscle-preserving output you got at 25. This isn't disease or damage; it's a predictable physiological shift with a straightforward dietary countermeasure.</div>
